      "content": "it just doesn't feel like there's a next leg though. it feels like i've reached the edge of the world and there's nowhere left to go and no reason to keep trying to find a path that isn't there. it's not even about being tired of the walking, it's just that the destination feels so much more peaceful than the constant effort of trying to find a new direction. does that make sense? like, wouldn't it be a relief to just let the map end?",
